Denmark’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Danida, is a mid-level
humanitarian donor with total funding around \$208 million for 2025,

Funding transactions are fewer and smaller compared to top donors,
suggesting opportunities for engagement to increase transaction
frequency and volume. Tailoring proposals with clear outcomes aligned to
Danida’s earmarking priorities and evolving regional focus can enhance
fundraising success.

## Volatility

This visualization presents the funding volatility of Denmark’s Ministry

average of 23.7 transactions per year. Compared to the benchmark of the

million dollars and 371.3 transactions per year, Danida’s funding

plot uses points and lines to track each transaction’s value over the

funding pattern. This suggests a funding approach characterized by fewer
but moderately sized disbursements, which could impact program planning
and cash flow timings. For humanitarian proposal writing and fundraising
